#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:3634
#, no-c-format
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr "Glosar"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:3637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Calendar Widget"
msgstr "Koledarski pripomočki"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A tool for choosing the date inside certain entry windows, such as the event "
"editing window. It is displayed as a small button to the right of the date "
"field. When you click the button, you will see a month calendar. Use the "
"arrows to go to a desired date, or click the month name or year number to go "
"directly to the desired month or year."
msgstr ""
"Orodje za izbiro datuma znotraj določenih vnosnih oken, kot je okno za "
"urejanje dogodkov. Prikaže se kot majhen gumb na desni strani datumskega "
"polja. Ko kliknete gumb, se prikaže mesečni koledar. S puščicami se "
"pomaknite na želeni datum ali kliknite ime meseca ali številko leta, da se "
"pomaknete neposredno na želeni mesec ali leto."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:3650
#, no-c-format
msgid "Date Navigator"
msgstr "Datumski navigator"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The calendar that is in the upper-left corner of the &korganizer; window. It "
"is the main way provided to navigate among dates, and to select from them. "
"The single-arrow icons move forwards and backwards in time by increments of "
"a month, while the double-arrows allow moving by a year at a time. Today's "
"date will be outlined with a small box. Dates which have events scheduled on "
"them will be bold. If you want to select a date, simply click it. Hold down "
"the &Ctrl; key and click the dates if you wish to select multiple "
"neighboring dates at once. The dates will be displayed in the main panel."
msgstr ""
"Koledar, ki je v zgornjem levem kotu &korganizer; okno. To je glavni način "
"za krmarjenje med datumi in izbiro med njimi. Ikone z eno puščico se "
"premikajo naprej in nazaj v času v korakih po mesec, medtem ko dvojne "
"puščice omogočajo premikanje za eno leto naenkrat. Današnji datum bo označen "
"z majhnim okvirčkom. Datumi, na katere so načrtovani dogodki, bodo označeni "
"krepko. Če želite izbrati datum, ga preprosto kliknite. Pridržite &Ctrl; in "
"kliknite na datume, če želite izbrati več sosednjih datumov hkrati. Datumi "
"bodo prikazani na glavni plošči."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Recurring events are not always displayed. You can prevent the display of "
"recurring appointments in the Date Navigator. Get more information in the "
"<link linkend=\"config-main-views\">Views chapter</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ponavljajoči se dogodki niso vedno prikazani. V Krmarju po datumih lahko "
"preprečite prikaz ponavljajočih se sestankov. Več informacij najdete v <link "
"linkend=\"config-main-views\">poglavju Pogledi</link>."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:3670
#, no-c-format
msgid "Due Date"
msgstr "Datum zapadlosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3673
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A due date is simply the date when your to-do must be finished. For "
"instance, if your to-do is that you must return your books to the library by "
"16th November, that date is called <quote>the to-do due date</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Rok je preprosto datum, ko mora biti vaše opravilo končano. Če je vaša "
"naloga na primer vrniti knjige v knjižnico do 16. novembra, se ta datum "
"imenuje <quote>rok za opravke</quote>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:3705
#, no-c-format
msgid "Main panel"
msgstr "Glavna plošča"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3707
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normally the largest part of the screen, to the right of the Date Navigator. "
"It displays the View of the Day, Workdays, Week or Month, the List View or "
"the To-do List view."
msgstr ""
"Običajno največji del zaslona, desno od Krmarja po datumih. Prikaže pogled "
"dneva, delovnih dni, tedna ali meseca, pogled seznama ali pogled seznama "
"opravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The right mouse button can be used in the List view and To-do List view "
"only. It displays a local menu. The left mouse button can be used in any "
"view."
msgstr ""
"Desni gumb miške lahko uporabite samo v pogledu seznama in pogledu seznama "
"opravil. Prikaže lokalni meni. Levi gumb miške lahko uporabite v katerem "
"koli pogledu."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:3717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Free/busy"
msgstr "Prosto/zasedeno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The free/busy information is a set of busy time intervals. By presenting the "
"intervals when one already has previous commitments, others can avoid "
"arranging appointments for these periods. Note that only the times are "
"published, not the event titles, descriptions or attendees. In other words, "
"the free/busy information is the availability schedule."
msgstr ""
"Informacije o prostem/zasedenem so nabor časovnih intervalov zasedenosti. S "
"predstavitvijo intervalov, ko ima nekdo že predhodne obveznosti, se lahko "
"drugi izognejo dogovarjanju za te termine. Upoštevajte, da so objavljeni le "
"časi, ne pa naslovi dogodkov, opisi ali udeleženci. Z drugimi besedami, "
"informacija o prostem/zasedenem je razpored razpoložljivosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:3724
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When adding attendees to your event, you need to know if they are busy or "
"free at that particular time before sending the invitations. If the "
"attendees make their free/busy information available, &korganizer; can "
"retrieve this information and display it in the <guilabel>Free/Busy</"
"guilabel> tab of the <guilabel>Edit Event</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Ko dodajate udeležence na svoj dogodek, morate vedeti, ali so ob določenem "
"času zasedeni ali prosti, preden pošljete povabila. Če udeleženci dajo na "
"voljo podatke o prostem/zasedenem, &korganizer; lahko pridobi te informacije "
"in jih prikaže na zavihku <guilabel>Prost/zaseden</guilabel> pogovornega "
"okna <guilabel>Urejanje dogodka</guilabel>."

